# Seldon Testing Standards

## Overview
This document defines the testing standards for the entire Seldon codebase. These standards ensure consistent, reliable, and maintainable tests that accurately reflect real-world usage patterns across all packages and systems.

## Core Principles

### 1. No Mock Data
- **Never use mocks** for core services (workspace, theme, compute, properties, etc.)
- Use actual services and real data structures
- Tests should reflect real usage patterns, not artificial scenarios
- Only mock external dependencies when absolutely necessary (APIs, file system, etc.)

### 2. Use Shared Fixtures and Test Data
- Import and use `WORKSPACE_FIXTURE` from `@seldon/core/helpers/fixtures/workspace` for complex workspace scenarios
- Use `testTheme` from `@seldon/core/themes/test-theme` for theme-related tests
- Use `import { customTheme } from "@seldon/core/themes"` for custom theme tests
- Create shared test data files for complex, reusable test scenarios

### 3. Minimal Test Data for Simple Cases
- Create minimal data objects for simple, focused tests
- Include only the necessary data for the specific test case
- Use real component IDs, theme values, and property structures

### 4. Test Both Success and Error Cases
- Always test the happy path (successful operations)
- Include error cases (non-existent nodes, invalid operations, etc.)
- Test edge cases and boundary conditions

### 5. Comprehensive Assertions
- Verify specific state changes, not just that something happened
- Check relationships between entities (parent-child, variant-instance, etc.)
- Verify that operations propagate correctly through hierarchies
- Test both the immediate effect and side effects
- Use precise assertions that validate the exact expected behavior

## Test Structure

### Basic Test Template
```typescript
import { describe, expect, it } from "bun:test"
import { Unit, ValueType } from "@seldon/core"
import { ComponentId, ComponentLevel } from "@seldon/core/components/constants"
import testTheme from "@seldon/core/themes/test-theme"
import { functionName } from "./function-name"

describe("functionName", () => {
  it("should [describe the expected behavior]", () => {
    const input = {
      // Minimal required data
    }

    const result = functionName(input)

    expect(result.property).toEqual(expectedValue)
  })

  it("should handle [error case description]", () => {
    const invalidInput = {
      // Invalid data
    }

    expect(() => {
      functionName(invalidInput)
    }).toThrow()
  })
})
```

### Complex Test Template (Using Fixtures)
```typescript
import { describe, expect, it } from "bun:test"
import { WORKSPACE_FIXTURE } from "@seldon/core/helpers/fixtures/workspace"
import testTheme from "@seldon/core/themes/test-theme"
import { functionName } from "./function-name"

describe("functionName", () => {
  it("should [describe complex behavior with propagation]", () => {
    // Check initial state
    expect(WORKSPACE_FIXTURE.byId["node-id"].children).toEqual([
      "child-1",
      "child-2",
    ])

    const result = functionName(
      {
        // Action payload
      },
      WORKSPACE_FIXTURE,
    )

    // Verify immediate effect
    expect(result.byId["node-id"].children).toEqual([
      "child-2",
      "child-1",
    ])

    // Verify propagation to instances
    expect(result.byId["instance-id"].children).toEqual([
      "instance-child-2",
      "instance-child-1",
    ])
  })
})
```

## Testing Patterns

### 1. Core System Tests (Properties, Compute, Themes)

#### Property Processing Tests
```typescript
import { describe, expect, it } from "bun:test"
import { ValueType } from "@seldon/core"
import { processNestedOverridesProps } from "./process-nested-overrides-props"

describe("processNestedOverridesProps", () => {
  it("should override properties using component-prefixed keys", () => {
    const properties = {
      content: { type: ValueType.EXACT, value: "Default Title" },
      color: { type: ValueType.THEME_CATEGORICAL, value: "@swatch.black" },
    }

    const nestedOverrides = {
      title: {
        content: "Custom Title",
        color: "@swatch.primary",
      },
    }

    const result = processNestedOverridesProps(
      properties,
      nestedOverrides,
      "title",
    )

    expect(result.content?.value).toBe("Custom Title")
    expect(result.color?.value).toBe("@swatch.primary")
    expect(result.color?.type).toBe(ValueType.THEME_CATEGORICAL)
  })
})
```

#### Compute System Tests
```typescript
import { expect, it } from "bun:test"
import { ComputedFunction, Properties, Unit, ValueType } from "@seldon/core"
import testTheme from "@seldon/core/themes/test-theme"
import { computeProperties } from "./compute-properties"

it("should compute properties with auto fit function", () => {
  const properties: Properties = {
    baseSize: {
      type: ValueType.EXACT,
      value: { unit: Unit.REM, value: 2 },
    },
    scaledSize: {
      type: ValueType.COMPUTED,
      value: {
        function: ComputedFunction.AUTO_FIT,
        input: {
          basedOn: "#baseSize",
          factor: 1.5,
        },
      },
    },
  }

  const result = computeProperties(properties, {
    properties,
    parentContext: null,
    theme: testTheme,
  })

  expect(result.scaledSize).toEqual({
    type: ValueType.EXACT,
    value: { unit: Unit.REM, value: 3 },
  })
})
```

#### CSS Generation Tests
```typescript
import { expect, it } from "bun:test"
import { Unit, ValueType } from "@seldon/core"
import testTheme from "@seldon/core/themes/test-theme"
import { getCssFromProperties } from "./get-css-from-properties"

it("Should return font styles if the properties are set", () => {
  expect(
    getCssFromProperties(
      {
        font: {
          preset: {
            type: ValueType.THEME_CATEGORICAL,
            value: "@font.title",
          },
          size: { type: ValueType.EMPTY, value: null },
        },
      },
      {
        properties: {},
        parentContext: null,
        theme: testTheme,
      },
      "button",
    ),
  ).toEqual(
    ".button {font-family: Inter;\nfont-weight: 500;\nfont-size: 1rem;\nline-height: 1.25;}",
  )
})
```

### 2. Factory Export Tests

#### Component Discovery Tests
```typescript
import { describe, expect, it } from "bun:test"
import { Workspace } from "@seldon/core"
import { ComponentId, ComponentLevel } from "@seldon/core/components/constants"
import { customTheme } from "@seldon/core/themes"
import { getComponentsToExport } from "./get-components-to-export"

describe("getComponentsToExport", () => {
  it("should return components to export from workspace", () => {
    const workspace: Workspace = {
      version: 1,
      customTheme,
      boards: {
        [ComponentId.BUTTON]: {
          id: ComponentId.BUTTON,
          label: "Button",
          order: 0,
          theme: "default",
          properties: {},
          variants: ["variant-button-default"],
        },
      },
      byId: {
        "variant-button-default": {
          id: "variant-button-default",
          component: ComponentId.BUTTON,
          level: ComponentLevel.ELEMENT,
          label: "Default",
          theme: "default",
          properties: {},
          isChild: false,
          type: "defaultVariant",
          fromSchema: true,
        },
      },
    }

    const result = getComponentsToExport(workspace, options, nodeIdToClass)

    expect(result).toHaveLength(1)
    expect(result[0]).toHaveProperty("name", "Button")
    expect(result[0]).toHaveProperty("componentId", ComponentId.BUTTON)
  })
})
```

### 3. Workspace System Tests

#### Property Setting Tests
```typescript
it("should set the properties of a node", () => {
  const workspace: Workspace = {
    version: 1,
    boards: {},
    byId: {
      "variant-button-default": {
        id: "variant-button-default",
        label: "Default",
        component: ComponentId.BUTTON,
        children: [],
        isChild: false,
        fromSchema: true,
        level: ComponentLevel.ELEMENT,
        theme: null,
        type: "defaultVariant",
        properties: {},
      },
    },
    customTheme,
  }

  const result = handleSetNodeProperties(
    {
      nodeId: "variant-button-default",
      properties: {
        screenWidth: {
          type: ValueType.EXACT,
          value: {
            value: 600,
            unit: Unit.PX,
          },
        },
      },
    },
    workspace,
  )

  expect(result.byId["variant-button-default"].properties).toEqual({
    screenWidth: {
      type: ValueType.EXACT,
      value: {
        value: 600,
        unit: Unit.PX,
      },
    },
  })
})
```

### 2. Node Manipulation Tests
```typescript
it("should move a child node within the same variant hierarchy", () => {
  // Check the initial state
  expect(WORKSPACE_FIXTURE.byId["parent-id"].children).toEqual([
    "child-1",
    "child-2",
  ])

  const { byId } = handleMoveNode(
    {
      nodeId: "child-1",
      target: {
        parentId: "parent-id",
        index: 1,
      },
    },
    WORKSPACE_FIXTURE,
  )

  // Verify the move operation
  expect(byId["parent-id"].children).toEqual([
    "child-2",
    "child-1",
  ])
})
```

### 3. Propagation Tests
```typescript
it("should propagate a move operation to all instances", () => {
  // Check initial variant structure (source of truth)
  expect(WORKSPACE_FIXTURE.byId["variant-button-default"].children).toEqual([
    "child-icon-K3GlMKHA",
    "child-label-wCHRir3I",
  ])

  // Check initial instances
  expect(WORKSPACE_FIXTURE.byId["child-button-4eo3qAPb"].children).toEqual([
    "child-icon-MAFDy9IN",
    "child-label-uhhihiiA",
  ])

  const { byId } = handleMoveNode(
    {
      nodeId: "child-icon-K3GlMKHA",
      target: {
        parentId: "variant-button-default",
        index: 1,
      },
    },
    WORKSPACE_FIXTURE,
  )

  // Verify variant change
  expect(byId["variant-button-default"].children).toEqual([
    "child-label-wCHRir3I",
    "child-icon-K3GlMKHA",
  ])

  // Verify instance propagation
  expect(byId["child-button-4eo3qAPb"].children).toEqual([
    "child-label-uhhiiA",
    "child-icon-MAFDy9IN",
  ])
})
```

### 4. Error Handling Tests
```typescript
it("should handle setting properties on a non-existent node", () => {
  const workspace: Workspace = {
    version: 1,
    boards: {},
    byId: {},
    customTheme,
  }

  expect(() => {
    handleSetNodeProperties(
      {
        nodeId: "non-existent-node",
        properties: {
          screenWidth: {
            type: ValueType.EXACT,
            value: {
              value: 600,
              unit: Unit.PX,
            },
          },
        },
      },
      workspace,
    )
  }).toThrow()
})
```

